Spring Boot вҖ” IoC & Dependency Injection (Notes Summary)
рҹ“Ң Image 1 вҖ” Core Concepts

Spring ecosystem:
- Spring is built on Java + XML config files
- Spring Framework вҶ’ Spring Boot (reduces config from 100s of files to ~50)
- Spring Boot = Spring Framework + auto-configuration

IoC вҖ” Inversion of Control:
- Full form: Invasion of Control (control is inverted вҖ” you don't create objects, Spring does)
- Without Spring: Student s = new Student();вқҢ (you manage it)
- With Spring: Spring handles creation вҶ’ managing вҶ’ destroying of objects вң…

Dependency Injection:
- Achieves loose coupling
- You just declare the dependency; Spring injects it for you

---

 рҹ“Ң Image 2 вҖ” IoC vs DI + IoC Container

| Term |            Nature               |
|------|---------------------------------|
| IoC  | Principle / Concept |
|  DI  | Design Pattern (implementation of IoC) |
| DI full form | Dependency Injection |

IoC Container:
- Lives inside the JVM (heap)
- Called the ApplicationContext
- Holds beans (e.g., Student() object) вҖ” Spring creates and stores them here

@Autowiring:
- Instead of `Student s = new Student();, you write @Autowired Student s;
- Spring fetches the object from the IoC container automatically

3 Types of Dependency Injection:
1. Field Injection вҖ” @Autowired on a field
2. Constructor Injection вҖ” via constructor
3. Setter Injection вҖ” via setter method

